@startuml
title Raspberry Pi State Diagram - User Authentication & Head Tracking

[*] --> INIT

INIT : Initialize Camera
INIT : Initialize CAN Interface
INIT : Load Registered User Data
INIT --> USER_AUTH

USER_AUTH : Capture face image
USER_AUTH : Identify user

USER_AUTH --> REQUEST_PRESSURE : Unknown user
USER_AUTH --> LOAD_USER_DATA : Known user

REQUEST_PRESSURE : Send pressure sensor request to STM via CAN
REQUEST_PRESSURE --> WAIT_PRESSURE

WAIT_PRESSURE : Receive pressure sensor value from STM
WAIT_PRESSURE --> MEASURE_HEAD_LENGTH : Head contact detected
WAIT_PRESSURE --> REQUEST_PRESSURE : Head contact not detected

MEASURE_HEAD_LENGTH : Measure front-back head length using camera
MEASURE_HEAD_LENGTH : Save measured head length
MEASURE_HEAD_LENGTH --> HEAD_POSITION_TRACKING

LOAD_USER_DATA : Load stored head length / user parameters
LOAD_USER_DATA --> HEAD_POSITION_TRACKING

HEAD_POSITION_TRACKING : Capture head position using camera
HEAD_POSITION_TRACKING : Calculate head coordinates (x, y, z)
HEAD_POSITION_TRACKING : Send (x, y, z) to STM via CAN

HEAD_POSITION_TRACKING --> HEAD_POSITION_TRACKING : Repeat tracking cycle

HEAD_POSITION_TRACKING --> ERROR : Camera error / CAN error
REQUEST_PRESSURE --> ERROR : CAN transmission error
WAIT_PRESSURE --> ERROR : CAN reception timeout
MEASURE_HEAD_LENGTH --> ERROR : Measurement failure

ERROR : Log error
ERROR : Try recovery
ERROR --> INIT : Recovery success
ERROR --> [*] : Critical failure

@enduml
